            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>The Treason of Stephen Arnold Douglas</head>
                <origin>New York Day Book</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>John Hancock</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>An article describing Douglas's supposed coalition with the Black
                    Republicans.</summary>
                <note/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>7</column>
                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>People in Texas who are suspected of being Abolitionists are being hanged
                    or kicked out of the state. Two map "pedlers" were just put on a ship to New
                    York because they were suspected of spying for the Abolitionists.</summary>
                <note/>
            </div>
            <pageNote>A short discussion of Walter Scott's early life in column 7.</pageNote>
        </page>
